  <scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_77d3789116b56cec374ae215ab18da1f">
    <head>Content Description</head>
<p>Collection contains drawings by Andrew Seager during his time as an architecture student at Cornell University.</p>  </scopecontent>
  <bioghist audience="internal" id="aspace_02833e474d4be057853c06d3a3f53451">
    <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
<p>Andrew Seager received a Bachelor of Architecture degree from Cornell University in 1965. He received a Master of Achitecture degree from Iowa State University, taught architectural design and history of architecture for a year at Iowa State, and then taught at Ball State University from 1968 until his retirement in 2008. Since his time at Cornell he has been associated with the Archaeological Exploration of Sardis, Turkey.</p>  </bioghist>
  <prefercite audience="internal" id="aspace_2db44cfdc0c3c553eefc56567ec833a9">
    <head>Preferred Citation</head>
<p>Andrew Seager student drawings, #37-5-4565. Division of Rare and Manuscript Collections, Cornell University Library.</p>  </prefercite>
  <relatedmaterial audience="internal" id="aspace_f904b92500d0f479efb5b8e763dfaa84">
    <head>Related Materials</head>
<p>See also the Andrew Seager Archives of the Built Environment at Ball State University <extref xlink:href="https://bsu.edu/academics/libraries/research/andrew-seager-archives-of-the-built-environment">https://bsu.edu/academics/libraries/research/andrew-seager-archives-of-the-built-environment</extref>. Seager served as director for this project.</p>  </relatedmaterial>
